reakage has again shown us that under the current model, `sktime` is vulnerable to interface changes in other packages at version zero. See #1478.\r\n\r\nShould we perhaps adopt a more defensive stance?\r\n\r\nMore precisely:\r\n\r\n* upper version bounds for *all* dependencies\r\n* at each release, we bump the upper bound to the current versions, or the highest versions that don't cause breakage\r\n* if at a release we cannot move the upper bound to current version, we open a maintenance issue to log this\r\n\r\nOpinions, @mloning, @aiwalter, @freddyaboulton?\r\n\r\n","closed_by":null,"reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/sktime/sktime/issues/1480/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/sktime/sktime/issues/1480/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":null}